The Minister of Energy Jeff Radebe has announced that fuel prices will be adjusted, effective from May 2. Radebe said that the adjustments of fuel prices have been informed by the current local and international factors. The fuel prices for May 2018 will be adjusted as follows: He added that the country’s fuel prices are adjusted monthly based on the international and local factors. “International factors include the fact that South Africa imports both crude oil and finished products at a price set at the international level, which includes importation costs.” He said that the rand depreciation against the dollar, the increase of Crude oil prices and deportation prices have contributed towards fuel prices adjustments. “The international prices of petroleum products increased on average during the period under review and this was in line with the higher crude oil prices.” -TNA Reporter